metadata.name: Distrust
metadata.description:
Distrust, a seed once planted  
Grows in the mind, a weed unchanted  
It starts with a hint of uncertainty  
A thought, a word, a hint of duplicity  
trust is like a garden, evergreen  
It needs to be nurtured, to be seen  
With time and care, it will grow strong  
And distrust, will be gone.
